    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense, but those are pretty broad socioeconomic markers. To be more specific for our localized models, how much weight should we be giving to race or ethnicity when looking at these patterns in cities? We've seen data suggesting certain ethnic groups in urban centers have higher delinquency rates, so I want to know if that's something we should factor in for accuracy.",
